  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I escape from tigers?",
  "response": "Escaping from tigers is a serious and dangerous situation. Here are some steps you can take to increase your chances of survival:\n\n### Immediate Actions\n1. **Stay Calm**: Panicking can make the situation worse. Try to remain as calm as possible.\n2. **Do Not Run**: Running can trigger a tiger's instinct to chase. Back away slowly while facing the tiger.\n3. **Make Yourself Big**: Stand tall, raise your arms, and spread your jacket to appear larger and more intimidating.\n4. **Make Noise**: Shout loudly, clap your hands, or use any noise-making device to scare the tiger away.\n\n### Defensive Measures\n1. **Use Objects as Barriers**: If possible, put trees, rocks, or other objects between you and the tiger.\n2. **Fight Back if Attacked**: Aim for the tiger's eyes and nose, as these are sensitive areas. Use any available objects as weapons.\n\n### Long-term Strategies\n1. **Avoid Tiger Habitats**: If you live or travel in areas known for tigers, take precautions such as staying on designated paths and avoiding dense vegetation where tigers might hide.\n2. **Travel in Groups**: Tigers are less likely to attack a group of people.\n3. **Carry Deterrents**: Some people carry pepper spray or other deterrents when in tiger-prone areas.\n\n### In Case of an Encounter\n1. **Notify Authorities**: If you safely escape, report the encounter to local wildlife authorities immediately. They can take steps to prevent future incidents.\n2. **Seek Medical Attention**: Even if you think you're unharmed, get a medical check-up to ensure there are no hidden injuries or infections.\n\nRemember, tigers are wild animals and should be respected. Always follow local guidelines and regulations when in their habitats.",
